</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir Edwin Landseer's Scene In Braemar - Highland Deer is expected to raise
Pounds 750,000 when it is sold at Christie's in March. The 8ft high painting
was last in the saleroom in 1888 when it sold for Pounds 5,456. It is the
Victorian artist's most important work to be auctioned since The Monarch of
the Glen was bought in 1916.
